k/page/NewsDetail/0,,10418~2259812,00.html| publisher =Sheffield United F.C.| date = 6 January 2011| accessdate = 6 January 2011}}</ref> In over a year after signing for the Blades, Conneely did not make a first team appearance, but he was a regular for the reserve team where he was the team captain.<ref name=ReserveCaptain>{{cite news|title=Alfreton Town sign Dagenham and Redbridge striker Adam Cunnington and Sheffield United defender Seamus Conneely on loan|url=http://www.chad.co.uk/sport/football/non-league-football/alfreton-town-sign-dagenham-and-redbridge-striker-adam-cunnington-and-sheffield-united-defender-seamus-conneely-on-loan-1-4327988|accessdate=9 March 2012|publisher=chad.co.uk|date=9 March 2012}}</ref> On 9 March 2012 Conneely joined [[Alfreton Town F.C.|Alfreton Town]] on loan for a month.<ref name=AlfretonLoan>{{cite news|title=Alfreton sign Seamus Conneely|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/0/football/17311782|accessdate=9 March 2012|publisher=BBC Sport|date=9 March 2012}}</ref> He made his Alfreton d\u00e9but the following day, coming on as a substitute after only 16 minutes away against [[Lincoln City F.C.|Lincoln City]] at [[Sincil Bank]] in a 1\u20130 victory for Alfreton Town.<ref name=\"Lin V Alf\">{{cite news|title=Lincoln City 0 Alfreton Town 1|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/0/football/17243663|accessdate=11 March 2012|publisher=BBC Sport|date=10 March 2012}}</ref> After returning to Sheffield United, Conneely was released when his contract expired in May 2012.<ref name=\"leave blades\">{{cite web|url=http://www.sufc.co.uk/page/NewsDetail/0,,10418~2792398,00.html|title=Trio offered new deals&nbsp;\u2013 11 released|publisher=Sheffield United F.C.|date=30 May 2012|access-date=30 May 2012|url-status=dead|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120602094408/http://www.sufc.co.uk/page/NewsDetail/0%2C%2C10418~2792398%2C00.html|archive-date=2 June 2012|df=dmy-all}}</ref>\n\n==International honours==\nConneely was capped for Ireland at several youth levels from under-17s and made his under-21s d\u00e9but against [[Switzerland national under-21 football team|Switzerland]] in October 2009.<ref name=\"u21 debut\">{{cite news| title = Owen Garvan's late goal earns Ireland U21 a draw| url = http://www.fai.ie/index.php?option=com_content&view=article&id=100443:owen-garvan-earns-ireland-u21-a-draw-against-switzerland&catid=3:under-21&Itemid=11#| publisher = fai.ie| date = 13 October 2009| accessdate = 3 August 2011}}</ref> He also represented Ireland in an under-23 team as part of the [[2009\u201311 International Challenge Trophy]].<ref name=\"u23 debut\">{{cite news| title = U23s defeat Estonia in Tallinn| url = http://www.fai.ie/index.php?option=com_content&view=article&id=101286:u23s-defeat-estonia-in-tallinn&catid=2:under-23&Itemid=10| publisher = fai.ie| date = 28 September 2010| accessdate = 3 August 2011}}</ref>\n\n==Career statistics==\n{{updated|match played 17 October 2015.}}\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align: center;\"\n|+ Club statistics\n|-\n!rowspan=\"2\"|Club\n!rowspan=\"2\"|Season\n!colspan=\"3\"|League\n!colspan=\"2\"|National Cup\n!colspan=\"2\"|League Cup\n!colspan=\"2\"|[[UEFA|Europe]]\n!colspan=\"2\"|Other\n!colspan=\"2\"|Total\n|-\n!Division!!Apps!!Goals!!Apps!!Goals!!Apps!!Goals!!Apps!!Goals!!Apps!!Goals!!Apps!!Goals\n|-\n|[[Sheffield United F.C.|Sheffield United]]\n|[[2011\u201312 Sheffield United F.C. season|2011\u201312]]<ref name=\"Games played by Seamus Conneely in 2011/2012\">{{Soccerbase season|55200|2011|access-date=8 June 2015}}</ref>\n|[[Football League One|League One]]\n|0||0||0||0||0||0||colspan=\"2\"|\u2014||0||0||0||0\n|-\n|[[Alfreton Town F.C.|Alfreton Town]] (loan)\n|[[2011\u201312 Football Conference|2011\u201312]]<ref name=\"Games played by Seamus Conneely in 2011/2012\"/>\n|[[Conference Premier]]\n|9||0||colspan=\"2\"|\u2014||colspan=\"2\"|\u2014||colspan=\"2\"|\u2014||colspan=\"2\"|\u2014||9||0\n|-\n|rowspan=\"4\"|[[Sligo Rovers F.C.|Sligo Rovers]]\n|[[2012 Sligo Rovers F.C. season|2012]]<ref name=\"Games played by Seamus Conneely - Soccerway\">{{Cite web\n| title = Games played by Seamus Conneely - Soccerway\n| url = https://int.soccerway.com/players/seamus-conneely/73896/\n| publisher = Soccerway\n| accessdate = 8 June 2015}}</ref>\n|rowspan=\"3\"|[[League of Ireland Premier Division|LOI Premier Division]]\n|13||1||colspan=\"2\"|\u2014||0||0||2<ref group=lower-alpha name=UEL>Appearances in [[UEFA Europa League]]</ref>||0||colspan=\"2\"|\u2014||15||1\n|-\n|[[2013 Sligo Rovers F.C. season|2013]]<ref name=\"Games played by Seamus Conneely - Soccerway\"/>\n|21||1||4||0||2||0||2<ref group=lower-alpha name=UCL>Appearances in [[UEFA Champions League]]</ref>||0||1<ref group=lower-alpha name=SC>Appearances in [[Setanta Sports Cup]]</ref>||0||30||1\n|-\n|[[2014 Sligo Rovers F.C. season|2014]]<ref name=\"Games played by Seamus Conneely - Soccerway\"/>\n|25||1||0||0||1||0||4<ref group=lower-alpha name=UEL/>||0||4<ref group=lower-alpha name=SC>Appearances in [[Setanta Sports Cup]]</ref>||0||34||1\n|-\n!colspan=\"2\"|Total\n!59!!3!!4!!0!!3!!0!!8!!0!!5!!0!!79!!3\n|-\n|rowspan=\"4\"|[[Accrington Stanley F.C.|Accrington Stanley]]\n|[[2014\u201315 Accrington Stanley F.C. season|2014\u201315]]<ref name=\"Games played by Seamus Conneely in 2014/2015\">{{Soccerbase season|55200|2014|access-date=8 June 2015}}</ref>\n|rowspan=\"3\"|[[Football League Two|League Two]]\n|16||3||colspan=\"2\"|\u2014||colspan=\"2\"|\u2014||colspan=\"2\"|\u2014||colspan=\"2\"|\u2014||16||3\n|-\n|[[2015\u201316 Accrington Stanley F.C. season|2015\u201316]]<ref name=\"Games played by Seamus Conneely in 2015/2016\">{{Soccerbase season|55200|2015|access-date=7 July 2017}}</ref>\n|46||3||1||0||1||0||colspan=\"2\"|---||3<ref group=lower-alpha name=MIX>One appearance in the [[Football League Trophy]] and two in the [[EFL League Two play-offs|League Two play-offs]]</ref>||0||51||3\n|-\n|[[2016-17 Accrington Stanley F.C. season|2016-17]]<ref name=\"Games played by Seamus Conneely in 2016/2017\">{{Soccerbase season|55200|2016|access-date=6 July 2017}}</ref>\n|38||1||4||0||3||0||colspan=\"2\"|---||1<ref group=lower-alpha name=FLT>Appearance in the [[Football League Trophy]]</ref>||0||46||1\n|-\n!colspan=\"2\"|Total\n!100!!7!!5!!0!!4!!0!!colspan=\"2\"|\u2014!!4!!0!!113!!7\n|-\n!colspan=\"3\"|Career total\n!168!!10!!9!!0!!7!!0!!8!!0!!9!!0!!201!!10\n|}\n\n{{Reflist|group=lower-alpha}}\n\n==Honours==\n;Sligo Rovers\n*[[League of Ireland]] (1): [[2012 League of Ireland|2012]]\n*[[FAI Cup]] (1): [[2013 FAI Cup|2013]]\n*[[Setanta Sports Cup]] (1): [[2014 Setanta Sports Cup|2014]]\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist|30em}}\n\n==External links==\n*{{Soccerbase}}\n* [http://www.theplayersagent.com/edit/profile/player/15072/seamus_conneely/match_lineups Seamus Conneely match lineups at theplayersagent ]\n* [http://www.galwayunitedfc.ie/first-team-squad/seamus-conneely.html Profile from official Galway United]\n*[http://www.soccerscene.ie/ss_gen/player.php?id=84&level=ss21 Republic of Ireland profile] at Soccer Scene\n\n{{Accrington Stanley F.C. squad}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Conneely, Seamus}}\n[[Category:1988 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Footballers from Lambeth]]\n[[Category:English footballers]]\n[[Category:Republic of Ireland association footballers]]\n[[Category:Republic of Ireland under-21 international footballers]]\n[[Category:Republic of Ireland under-23 international footballers]]\n[[Category:Association football defenders]]\n[[Category:Association football midfielders]]\n[[Category:Mervue United A.F.C. players]]\n[[Category:Galway United F.C. (1937\u20132011) players]]\n[[Category:Sheffield United F.C. players]]\n[[Category:Alfreton Town F.C. players]]\n[[Category:Sligo Rovers F.C. players]]\n[[Category:Accrington Stanley F.C. players]]\n[[Category:League of Ireland players]]\n[[Category:English Football League players]]\n[[Category:National League (English football) players]]\n", "name_user": "GiantSnowman", "label": "safe", "comment": "clean up", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Seamus_Conneely"}
{"title_page": "Red-light districts in Belgium", "text_new": "Prostitution is legal in Belgium, but related activities such as organising prostitution and other forms of [[pimping]] are illegal.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://2001-2009.state.gov/g/drl/rls/hrrpt/2007/100550.htm |title=Country Report on Human Rights Practices in Belgium |publisher=State.gov |date=2008-03-11 |accessdate=2010-03-31}}</ref> Enforcement varies, and in some areas brothels are unofficially tolerated.\n\nMost of the [[red-light districts]] (RLDs) in [[Belgium]] are made up of windows (where the [[prostitutes]] sit, usually scantily dressed, trying to entice customers in) although some [[street prostitution]] does occur.\n\n==Red-light districts by city==\n===Brussels===\n[[Image:Aarschotstraat.jpg|thumb|[[Rue d'Aerschot]], Brussels]]\nThe main red light district in [[Brussels]] is north of the [[Brussels-North railway station|Gare du Nord]]. In [[Rue d'Aerschot]], Rue de Brabant and the surrounding side-streets there are [[sex shops]] and many windows where prostitutes sit.<ref name=\"redlight\">{{cite web |url= http://www.redlightdistricts.net/red-light-districts-in-belgium/ |title= Red light districts in Belgium |last= |first= |date= 31 August 2017 |website= Red Light Districts |publisher= |access-date= 29 October 2017 |quote= }}</ref> Most of the prostitutes near the Gare du Nord, including Rue d'Aerschot, are Romanian and Bulgarian. Further away from the station the girls are more from [[Ghana]] and [[Nigeria]].<ref name=\"ofsd\">{{cite web |url= http://www.beobachtungsstelle-gesellschaftspolitik.de/f/18c81917c6.pdf |title= Prostitution in Belgium: federal legislation and regulation at the local level |last= Reinschmidt |first= Lena |date= June 2016 |website= |publisher= Observatory for Sociopolitical Developments in Europe |access-date= 1 November 2017 |quote= }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url= http://youropeans.eu/brussels/monique |title= MONIQUE SEX WORKER  |last= |first= |date= |website= Eouropeans |publisher= |access-date= 29 October 2017 |quote= }}</ref>\n\nThe Alhambra Quarter of Brussels (South-west of the Gare du Nord) has traditionally been an area where street prostitution has occurred.<ref name=\"rlde\">{{cite web |url= http://www.rld-europa.com/ |title= Red Light Districts - Belgium |last= |first= |date= |website= RLD-Europa |publisher= |access-date= 29 October 2017 |quote= }}</ref> There have been numerous attempts to ban street prostitution from the area. In 2012, new regulations were introduced to restrict the girls and also to punish [[Kerb crawler|kerb-crawlers]].<ref name=\"reframing\">{{cite book |last1= Persak |first1= Nina |last2= Vermeulen |first2= Gert |date= 2014 |title= Reframing prostitution: from discourse to description, from moralisation to normalisation? |url= |location= |publisher= Maklu Pub |page= |isbn= 978-9046606735 |author-link= }}</ref> A new city regulation in 2016 banned the prostitutes from the area and proposed a new tolerance zone nearer the Gare du Nord. This was overturned by the Council of State at the end of 2016.<ref name=\"rlde\" />\n\nA second, smaller area of street prostitution is along [[Avenue Louise]], where street walkers ply their trade at night.<ref name=\"redlight\" />\n\nGay prostitution occurs around the Place Fontainas.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Helm |first1=Sarah |title=Gays under pressure in Belgium's moral backlash Anger over child |url=https://www.independent.co.uk/news/world/gays-under-pressure-in-belgiums-moral-backlash-anger-over-child-murders-switches-to-belgiums-gays-1354281.html |website=The Independent |accessdate=1 February 2019 |language=en |date=26 November 1996}}</ref>\n\n===Antwerp===\nIn [[Antwerp]] prostitution is only permitted in the area bounded by Verversrui, Vingerlingstraat and Schippersstraat,<ref name=\"redlight\" /> locally knows as 'schipperskwartier' (shipper's quarters).<ref name=\"amster\">{{cite web |url= http://www.amsterdam-red-light-district-maps.com/Antwerp.html |title= Antwerp's Red Light District |last= |first= |date= |website= Amsterdam Red Light District Maps, Photos, Hotels, Videos |publisher= |access-date= 29 October 2017 |quote= }}</ref>\n\nProstitution in the city was previously run by gangs and violence was common.<ref name=\"business\">{{cite web |url= http://www.businessinsider.com/antwerps-red-light-district-2013-11?IR=T |title= Why Antwerp Has The Best-Run Sex District In The World |last= Fuchs |first= Erin |date= 21 November 2013 |website= Business Insider |publisher= |access-date= 29 October 2017 |quote= }}</ref> In the year 2000 the city, led by the mayor, started a clean-up operation. The areas in which prostitution was allowed was reduced to the Schipperskwartier, and a permit system was introduced. The permits for owners of the windows have to be personally signed by the mayor.<ref name=\"business\" /> This helps to keep organised crime out of the area.\n\nThe area was refurbished and pedestrianised in an attempt to get away from the previous seedy-looking image. Usually, windows in red light districts are isolated from one another, but the windows here are interconnected in groups of 3, 5 or 7 so the prostitutes may socialise with each other and also aid each other in the event of trouble with a client.<ref name=\"business\" /> There is a small police station within the area,<ref name=\"redlight\" /> but the police keep a low profile.<ref name=\"amster\" />\n\nBetween Verversrui and Schippersstraat is the ''Villa Tinto''. Previously an industrial building, it has been converted by architect [[Arne Quinze]]<ref name=\"independent\">{{cite web |url= https://www.independent.co.uk/news/world/europe/passports-and-panic-buttons-in-the-brothel-of-the-future-417159.html |title= Passports and panic buttons in the brothel of the future |last= Castle  |first= Stephen |date= 22 September 2006 |website= [[The Independent]] |publisher= |access-date= 29 October 2017 |quote= }}</ref> and Flemish interior designers into a complex with 51 windows<ref name=\"independent\" /> on the ground floor with a doctor's practice and bed & breakfast rooms above.<ref name=\"redlight\" /> The project was set up by Franky De Coninck, a respected Belgian businessman.<ref name=\"independent\" /> It has been called \"Europe's most high tech bordello\".<ref name=\"amster\" /> Opened in 2005,<ref name=\"amster\" /> it opens seven days a week with about a 305 girls working there in shifts.<ref name=\"redlight\" /> In an attempt to prevent [[human trafficking]], only women with EU passports can work there and there are biometric keypads to the rooms so there can be no subletting.<ref name=\"independent\" /> Each room has a panic button in case of trouble.<ref name=\"independent\" />\n\n===Charleroi===\nProstitution in [[Charleroi]] formally took place in various places over the city. In 2002 the council limited the activity to a small area, known as the \"Charleroi Triangle\"<ref name=\"entre\" /> (intersection of rue du Moulin, rue de Marchienne, rue Arthur Pater, rue de la Fenderie and place Rucloux).<ref name=\"redlight\" /> The city started planning to redevelop the \"Lower City\", including the Triangle,<ref name=\"entre\" /> and in 2011 the trade was forced to relocate to the area around the minist\u00e8re des Finances (rue des Rivages, rue Monnet, la place des Tramways and rue du Grand Central).<ref name=\"rlde\" /><ref name=\"entre\">{{cite web |url= https://www.entre2wallonie.com/historique |title= Prostitution \u00e0 Charleroi |last= |first= |date= |website= Entre 2 Wallonie |publisher= |access-date= 31 October 2017 |language= French }}</ref> The new area was thought to be less secure than the triangle by the prostitutes<ref>{{cite web |url= https://www.rtbf.be/info/regions/detail_charleroi-le-quartier-chaud-se-deplace?id=6405613 |title= Charleroi : le quartier chaud se d\u00e9place |last= |first= |date= 5 July 2011 |website= FTBF |publisher= |access-date= 31 October 2017 |language= French }}</ref> and attempts were made to move back to the old area.<ref name=\"rlde\" />\n\nStreet prostitution was prevalent in Gosselie on the northern outskirts of Charleroi. In June 2011 this was limited to the area behind the TEC Charleroi buildings. The prostitutes disregarded this limit,  prompting a total ban on street prostitution in 2014.<ref name=\"entre\" /><ref name=\"rtbf\">{{cite web |url= https://www.rtbf.be/info/regions/detail_la-prostitution-en-rue-desormais-interdite-sur-le-territoire-de-charleroi?id=8393661 |title= La prostitution en rue d\u00e9sormais interdite sur le territoire de Charleroi |last= |first= |date= 4 November 2014 |website= RTBF |publisher= |access-date= 29 October 2017 |language= French }}</ref> Also in Gosselie are some drinking establishments where prostitution is allowed. These are on faubourg de Bruxelles and the [[N5 road (Belgium)|N5]].<ref name=\"rlde\" /><ref name=\"rtbf\" />\n\n===Deinze===\nIn [[Deinze]] there are a few windows along the Kortrijksesteenweg (N43).<ref name=\"rlde\" /> The road has been nicknamed \"Rue d'amour\".\n\n===Ghent===\n[[File:Glazenstraat Gent.jpg|thumb|Glazen Straatje]]\nThere are two red-light districts in [[Ghent]], located close to each other.<ref name=\"rlde\" /><ref name=\"amster2\">{{cite web |url= http://www.amsterdam-red-light-district-maps.com/Ghent.html |title= Ghent Red Light District / Quartier Rouge Gand / Rosse Buurt Gent |last= |first= |date= |website= Amsterdam Red Light District Maps, Photos, Hotels, Videos |publisher= |access-date= 29 October 2017 |quote= }}</ref> The larger is in Schepenenvijverstraat and Pieter Vanderdoncktdoorgang including Glazen Straatje (a glass roofed arcade). There are just under 70 windows here.<ref name=\"amster2\" /> The second area is situated in Belgradostraat, and has about 30 windows.<ref name=\"amster2\" />\n\nFollowing pressure from locals, the prostitutes in the windows in Ghent dress in a respectable fashion.<ref name=\"redlight\" />\n\n===Liege===\nRue Varin, in the Li\u00e8ge-Cath\u00e9drale quarter had been a centre on prostitution since the 19th century. The area was partially demolished in the early 2000s for the rebuilding of [[Li\u00e8ge-Guillemins railway station]]. The remaining building were renovated as part of the gentrification of the area and prostitution stopped.<ref>{{cite web |url= http://www.lalibre.be/regions/liege/rue-varin-l-exode-des-petites-dames-51b899a6e4b0de6db9b1f232 |title= Rue Varin : l'exode des petites dames |last= BECHET |first= MARC |date= 31 March 2008 |website= La Libre |publisher= |access-date= 12 November 2017 |language= French }}</ref>\n\nThere was a window area in [[Liege]] centred around Rue du Champion and Rue de l\u2019Agneau near the [[Meuse|River Meuse's]] west bank.<ref name=\"redlight\" /> This was shut in 2009<ref name=\"sud\">{{cite web |url= http://www.sudinfo.be/1243063/article/2015-03-19/prostitution-a-liege-elles-tapinent-pour-payer-leur-loyer |title= Prostitution \u00e0 Li\u00e8ge: elles tapinent pour payer leur loyer |last= |first= |date= 19 March 2015  |website= Sud Info |publisher= |access-date= 29 October 2017 |language= French }}</ref> Street prostitution has been a problem in this area and also around Grand Poste since the windows were closed.<ref name=\"sud\" /> Following the shutting of the windows, about 180 prostitutes moved to [[Seraing]].<ref name=\"sudinfo\">{{cite web |url= http://www.sudinfo.be/1250328/article/2015-03-27/pas-d-eros-center-a-liege-ou-vont-aller-les-184-prostituees-de-seraing-qui-pensa |title= Pas d'Eros Center \u00e0 Li\u00e8ge: o\u00f9 vont aller les 184 prostitu\u00e9es de Seraing qui pensaient revenir? |last= Gochel |first= Luc  |date= 28 March 2015 |website= Sud Info |publisher=  |access-date= 29 October 2017 |language= French }}</ref> The council had planned to build an \"Eros Centre\" for the prostitutes to work in but this was cancelled.<ref name=\"sudinfo\" />\n\n===Ostend===\nThere have been windows in various streets in the docklands area of [[Ostend]] - Langestraat, Hazegras, Fregatstraat, Vrijhavenstraat and Oesterbankstraat.<ref name=\"rlde\" /> Ostend council have been trying to clean the area up and many establishments have closed.\n\n===Seraing===\nThere are a number of windows in rue Marnix, [[Seraing]].<ref name=\"rlde\" /><ref name=\"rte\">{{cite web |url= https://www.rtc.be/video/info/seraing-prostitution_1491446_325.html |title= Seraing prostitution |last= |first= |date= 18 March 2011 |website= RTE Tele Liege |publisher= |access-date= 29 October 2017 |quote= }}</ref><ref name=\"seraing\">{{cite web |url= http://www.seraing.be//?s=Eros+Center&x=0&y=0 |title= Eros Center |last= |first= |date= 17 February 2015 |website= Seraing |publisher= |access-date= 29 October 2017 |quote= }}</ref> There were about 100 prostitutes working there until the shutting of the windows in Liege, when about 180 prostitutes moved to Seraing.<ref name=\"sudinfo\" />\n\nThe council plan to stop prostitution in rue Marnix and build a new \"Eros Centre\".<ref name=\"rte\" /><ref name=\"seraing\" /><ref name=\"sudinfo\" /> The centre will have 34 working rooms, a medical office, police station and a car park. Activities within the centre will be screened from the passing public.<ref name=\"seraing\" />\n\n===Sint-Truiden===\nThere are a number of windows along Luikersteenweg, [[Sint-Truiden]]. It is known locally as \"Chauss\u00e9e d'Amour\".<ref name=\"rlde\" /><ref name=\"hln\" /> Currently, there are 42 brothel permits issued, but the mayor of Sint-Truiden wants to tighten up on the establishments. Weekly checks on working conditions and work permits are carried out by the local police.<ref name=\"hln\">{{cite web |url= https://m.hln.be/nieuws/binnenland/prostituees-op-chaussee-d-amour-werken-voor-amper-25-euro~a9cba99e/ |title= Prostituees op Chauss\u00e9e d'Amour werken voor amper 25 euro |last= |first= |date= 1 June 2017 |website= HLN |publisher= |access-date= 29 October 2017 |quote= }}</ref>\n\n== Further reading==\n* {{cite book |last= Weitzer |first= Ronald |date= 21 December 2012 |title= Legalizing Prostitution: From Illicit Vice to Lawful Business |url= |location= |publisher= [[NYU Press]] |page= |isbn= 978-0814794647 |author-link= Ronald Weitzer }}\n* {{cite book |last1= Persak |first1= Nina |last2= Vermeulen |first2= Gert |date= 2014 |title= Reframing prostitution: from discourse to description, from moralisation to normalisation? |url= |location= |publisher= Maklu Pub |page= |isbn= 978-9046606735 |author-link= }}\n\n==See also==\n* [[Prostitution in Belgium]]\n* [[Red-light district]]\n* [[List of red-light districts]]\n\n==References==\n{{reflist|2}}\n\n[[Category:Prostitution in Belgium]]\n[[Category:Red-light districts in Belgium| ]]\n", "text_old": "Prostitution is legal in Belgium, but related activities such as organising prostitution and other forms of [[pimping]] are illegal.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://2001-2009.state.gov/g/drl/rls/hrrpt/2007/100550.htm |title=Country Report on Human Rights Practices in Belgium |publisher=State.gov |date=2008-03-11 |accessdate=2010-03-31}}</ref> Enforcement varies, and in some areas brothels are unofficially tolerated.\n\nMost of the [[red-light districts]] (RLDs) in [[Belgium]] are made up of windows (where the [[prostitutes]] sit, usually scantily dressed, trying to entice customers in) although some [[street prostitution]] does occur.\n\n==Red-light districts by city==\n===Brussels===\n[[Image:Aarschotstraat.jpg|thumb|[[Rue d'Aerschot]], Brussels]]\nThe main red light district in [[Brussels]] is north of the [[Brussels-North railway station|Gare du Nord]]. In [[Rue d'Aerschot]], Rue de Brabant and the surrounding side-streets there are [[sex shops]] and many windows where prostitutes sit.<ref name=\"redlight\">{{cite web |url= http://www.redlightdistricts.net/red-light-districts-in-belgium/ |title= Red light districts in Belgium |last= |first= |date= 31 August 2017 |website= Red Light Districts |publisher= |access-date= 29 October 2017 |quote= }}</ref> Most of the prostitutes near the Gare du Nord, including Rue d'Aerschot, are Romanian and Bulgarian. Further away from the station the girls are more from [[Ghana]] and [[Nigeria]].<ref name=\"ofsd\">{{cite web |url= http://www.beobachtungsstelle-gesellschaftspolitik.de/f/18c81917c6.pdf |title= Prostitution in Belgium: federal legislation and regulation at the local level |last= Reinschmidt |first= Lena |date= June 2016 |website= |publisher= Observatory for Sociopolitical Developments in Europe |access-date= 1 November 2017 |quote= }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url= http://youropeans.eu/brussels/monique |title= MONIQUE SEX WORKER  |last= |first= |date= |website= Eouropeans |publisher= |access-date= 29 October 2017 |quote= }}</ref>\n\nThe Alhambra Quarter of Brussels (South-west of the Gare du Nord) has traditionally been an area where street prostitution has occurred.<ref name=\"rlde\">{{cite web |url= http://www.rld-europa.com/ |title= Red Light Districts - Belgium |last= |first= |date= |website= RLD-Europa |publisher= |access-date= 29 October 2017 |quote= }}</ref> There have been numerous attempts to ban street prostitution from the area. In 2012, new regulations were introduced to restrict the girls and also to punish [[Kerb crawler|kerb-crawlers]].<ref name=\"reframing\">{{cite book |last1= Persak |first1= Nina |last2= Vermeulen |first2= Gert |date= 2014 |title= Reframing prostitution: from discourse to description, from moralisation to normalisation? |url= |location= |publisher= Maklu Pub |page= |isbn= 978-9046606735 |author-link= }}</ref> A new city regulation in 2016 banned the prostitutes from the area and proposed a new tolerance zone nearer the Gare du Nord. This was overturned by the Council of State at the end of 2016.<ref name=\"rlde\" />\n\nA second, smaller area of street prostitution is along [[Avenue Louise]], where street walkers ply their trade at night.<ref name=\"redlight\" />\n\nGay prostitution occurs around the Place Fontainas.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Helm |first1=Sarah |title=Gays under pressure in Belgium's moral backlash Anger over child |url=https://www.independent.co.uk/news/world/gays-under-pressure-in-belgiums-moral-backlash-anger-over-child-murders-switches-to-belgiums-gays-1354281.html |website=The Independent |accessdate=1 February 2019 |language=en |date=26 November 1996}}</ref>\n\n===Antwerp===\nIn [[Antwerp]] prostitution is only permitted in the area bounded by Verversrui, Vingerlingstraat and Schippersstraat,<ref name=\"redlight\" /> locally knows as 'schipperskwartier' (shipper's quarters).<ref name=\"amster\">{{cite web |url= http://www.amsterdam-red-light-district-maps.com/Antwerp.html |title= Antwerp's Red Light District |last= |first= |date= |website= Amsterdam Red Light District Maps, Photos, Hotels, Videos |publisher= |access-date= 29 October 2017 |quote= }}</ref>\n\nProstitution in the city was previously run by gangs and violence was common.<ref name=\"business\">{{cite web |url= http://www.businessinsider.com/antwerps-red-light-district-2013-11?IR=T |title= Why Antwerp Has The Best-Run Sex District In The World |last= Fuchs |first= Erin |date= 21 November 2013 |website= Business Insider |publisher= |access-date= 29 October 2017 |quote= }}</ref> In the year 2000 the city, led by the mayor, started a clean-up operation. The areas in which prostitution was allowed was reduced to the Schipperskwartier, and a permit system was introduced. The permits for owners of the windows have to be personally signed by the mayor.<ref name=\"business\" /> This helps to keep organised crime out of the area.\n\nThe area was refurbished and pedestrianised in an attempt to get away from the previous seedy-looking image. Usually, windows in red light districts are isolated from one another, but the windows here are interconnected in groups of 3, 5 or 7 so the prostitutes may socialise with each other and also aid each other in the event of trouble with a client.<ref name=\"business\" /> There is a small police station within the area,<ref name=\"redlight\" /> but the police keep a low profile.<ref name=\"amster\" />\n\nBetween Verversrui and Schippersstraat is the ''Villa Tinto''. Previously an industrial building, it has been converted by architect [[Arne Quinze]]<ref name=\"independent\">{{cite web |url= https://www.independent.co.uk/news/world/europe/passports-and-panic-buttons-in-the-brothel-of-the-future-417159.html |title= Passports and panic buttons in the brothel of the future |last= Castle  |first= Stephen |date= 22 September 2006 |website= [[The Independent]] |publisher= |access-date= 29 October 2017 |quote= }}</ref> and Flemish interior designers into a complex with 51 windows<ref name=\"independent\" /> on the ground floor with a doctor's practice and bed & breakfast rooms above.<ref name=\"redlight\" /> The project was set up by Franky De Coninck, a respected Belgian businessman.<ref name=\"independent\" /> It has been called \"Europe's most high tech bordello\".<ref name=\"amster\" /> Opened in 2005,<ref name=\"amster\" /> it opens seven days a week with about a 305 girls working there in shifts.<ref name=\"redlight\" /> In an attempt to prevent [[human trafficking]], only women with EU passports can work there and there are biometric keypads to the rooms so there can be no subletting.<ref name=\"independent\" /> Each room has a panic button in case of trouble.<ref name=\"independent\" />\n\n===Charleroi===\nProstitution in [[Charleroi]] formally took place in various places over the city. In 2002 the council limited the activity to a small area, known as the \"Charleroi Triangle\"<ref name=\"entre\" /> (intersection of rue du Moulin, rue de Marchienne, rue Arthur Pater, rue de la Fenderie and place Rucloux).<ref name=\"redlight\" /> The city started planning to redevelop the \"Lower City\", including the Triangle,<ref name=\"entre\" /> and in 2011 the trade was forced to relocate to the area around the minist\u00e8re des Finances (rue des Rivages, rue Monnet, la place des Tramways and rue du Grand Central).<ref name=\"rlde\" /><ref name=\"entre\">{{cite web |url= https://www.entre2wallonie.com/historique |title= Prostitution \u00e0 Charleroi |last= |first= |date= |website= Entre 2 Wallonie |publisher= |access-date= 31 October 2017 |language= French }}</ref> The new area was thought to be less secure than the triangle by the prostitutes<ref>{{cite web |url= https://www.rtbf.be/info/regions/detail_charleroi-le-quartier-chaud-se-deplace?id=6405613 |title= Charleroi : le quartier chaud se d\u00e9place |last= |first= |date= 5 July 2011 |website= FTBF |publisher= |access-date= 31 October 2017 |language= French }}</ref> and attempts were made to move back to the old area.<ref name=\"rlde\" />\n\nStreet prostitution was prevalent in Gosselie on the northern outskirts of Charleroi. In June 2011 this was limited to the area behind the TEC Charleroi buildings. The prostitutes disregarded this limit,  prompting a total ban on street prostitution in 2014.<ref name=\"entre\" /><ref name=\"rtbf\">{{cite web |url= https://www.rtbf.be/info/regions/detail_la-prostitution-en-rue-desormais-interdite-sur-le-territoire-de-charleroi?id=8393661 |title= La prostitution en rue d\u00e9sormais interdite sur le territoire de Charleroi |last= |first= |date= 4 November 2014 |website= RTBF |publisher= |access-date= 29 October 2017 |language= French }}</ref> Also in Gosselie are some drinking establishments where prostitution is allowed. These are on faubourg de Bruxelles and the [[N5 road (Belgium)|N5]].<ref name=\"rlde\" /><ref name=\"rtbf\" />\n\n===Deinze===\nIn [[Deinze]] there are a few windows along the Kortrijksesteenweg (N43).<ref name=\"rlde\" /> The road has been nicknamed \"Rue d'amour\".\n\n===Ghent===\n[[File:Glazenstraat Gent.jpg|thumb|Glazen Straatje]]\nThere are two red-light districts in [[Ghent]], located close to each other.<ref name=\"rlde\" /><ref name=\"amster2\">{{cite web |url= http://www.amsterdam-red-light-district-maps.com/Ghent.html |title= Ghent Red Light District / Quartier Rouge Gand / Rosse Buurt Gent |last= |first= |date= |website= Amsterdam Red Light District Maps, Photos, Hotels, Videos |publisher= |access-date= 29 October 2017 |quote= }}</ref> The larger is in Schepenenvijverstraat and Pieter Vanderdoncktdoorgang including Glazen Straatje (a glass roofed arcade). There are just under 70 windows here.<ref name=\"amster2\" /> The second area is situated in Belgradostraat, and has about 30 windows.<ref name=\"amster2\" />\n\nFollowing pressure from locals, the prostitutes in the windows in Ghent dress in a respectable fashion.<ref name=\"redlight\" />\n\n===Liege===\nRue Varin, in the Li\u00e8ge-Cath\u00e9drale quarter had been a centre on prostitution since the 19th century. The area was partially demolished in the early 2000's for the rebuilding of [[Li\u00e8ge-Guillemins railway station]]. The remaining building were renovated as part of the gentrification of the area and prostitution stopped.<ref>{{cite web |url= http://www.lalibre.be/regions/liege/rue-varin-l-exode-des-petites-dames-51b899a6e4b0de6db9b1f232 |title= Rue Varin : l'exode des petites dames |last= BECHET |first= MARC |date= 31 March 2008 |website= La Libre |publisher= |access-date= 12 November 2017 |language= French }}</ref>\n\nThere was a window area in [[Liege]] centred around Rue du Champion and Rue de l\u2019Agneau near the [[Meuse|River Meuse's]] west bank.<ref name=\"redlight\" /> This was shut in 2009<ref name=\"sud\">{{cite web |url= http://www.sudinfo.be/1243063/article/2015-03-19/prostitution-a-liege-elles-tapinent-pour-payer-leur-loyer |title= Prostitution \u00e0 Li\u00e8ge: elles tapinent pour payer leur loyer |last= |first= |date= 19 March 2015  |website= Sud Info |publisher= |access-date= 29 October 2017 |language= French }}</ref> Street prostitution has been a problem in this area and also around Grand Poste since the windows were closed.<ref name=\"sud\" /> Following the shutting of the windows, about 180 prostitutes moved to [[Seraing]].<ref name=\"sudinfo\">{{cite web |url= http://www.sudinfo.be/1250328/article/2015-03-27/pas-d-eros-center-a-liege-ou-vont-aller-les-184-prostituees-de-seraing-qui-pensa |title= Pas d'Eros Center \u00e0 Li\u00e8ge: o\u00f9 vont aller les 184 prostitu\u00e9es de Seraing qui pensaient revenir? |last= Gochel |first= Luc  |date= 28 March 2015 |website= Sud Info |publisher=  |access-date= 29 October 2017 |language= French }}</ref> The council had planned to build an \"Eros Centre\" for the prostitutes to work in but this was cancelled.<ref name=\"sudinfo\" />\n\n===Ostend===\nThere have been windows in various streets in the docklands area of [[Ostend]] - Langestraat, Hazegras, Fregatstraat, Vrijhavenstraat and Oesterbankstraat.<ref name=\"rlde\" /> Ostend council have been trying to clean the area up and many establishments have closed.\n\n===Seraing===\nThere are a number of windows in rue Marnix, [[Seraing]].<ref name=\"rlde\" /><ref name=\"rte\">{{cite web |url= https://www.rtc.be/video/info/seraing-prostitution_1491446_325.html |title= Seraing prostitution |last= |first= |date= 18 March 2011 |website= RTE Tele Liege |publisher= |access-date= 29 October 2017 |quote= }}</ref><ref name=\"seraing\">{{cite web |url= http://www.seraing.be//?s=Eros+Center&x=0&y=0 |title= Eros Center |last= |first= |date= 17 February 2015 |website= Seraing |publisher= |access-date= 29 October 2017 |quote= }}</ref> There were about 100 prostitutes working there until the shutting of the windows in Liege, when about 180 prostitutes moved to Seraing.<ref name=\"sudinfo\" />\n\nThe council plan to stop prostitution in rue Marnix and build a new \"Eros Centre\".<ref name=\"rte\" /><ref name=\"seraing\" /><ref name=\"sudinfo\" /> The centre will have 34 working rooms, a medical office, police station and a car park. Activities within the centre will be screened from the passing public.<ref name=\"seraing\" />\n\n===Sint-Truiden===\nThere are a number of windows along Luikersteenweg, [[Sint-Truiden]]. It is known locally as \"Chauss\u00e9e d'Amour\".<ref name=\"rlde\" /><ref name=\"hln\" /> Currently, there are 42 brothel permits issued, but the mayor of Sint-Truiden wants to tighten up on the establishments. Weekly checks on working conditions and work permits are carried out by the local police.<ref name=\"hln\">{{cite web |url= https://m.hln.be/nieuws/binnenland/prostituees-op-chaussee-d-amour-werken-voor-amper-25-euro~a9cba99e/ |title= Prostituees op Chauss\u00e9e d'Amour werken voor amper 25 euro |last= |first= |date= 1 June 2017 |website= HLN |publisher= |access-date= 29 October 2017 |quote= }}</ref>\n\n== Further reading==\n* {{cite book |last= Weitzer |first= Ronald |date= 21 December 2012 |title= Legalizing Prostitution: From Illicit Vice to Lawful Business |url= |location= |publisher= [[NYU Press]] |page= |isbn= 978-0814794647 |author-link= Ronald Weitzer }}\n* {{cite book |last1= Persak |first1= Nina |last2= Vermeulen |first2= Gert |date= 2014 |title= Reframing prostitution: from discourse to description, from moralisation to normalisation? |url= |location= |publisher= Maklu Pub |page= |isbn= 978-9046606735 |author-link= }}\n\n==See also==\n* [[Prostitution in Belgium]]\n* [[Red-light district]]\n* [[List of red-light districts]]\n\n==References==\n{{reflist|2}}\n\n[[Category:Prostitution in Belgium]]\n[[Category:Red-light districts in Belgium| ]]\n", "name_user": "Alistair1978", "label": "safe", "comment": "typo (viaWP:JWB)", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Red-light_districts_in_Belgium"}
